            "answer_text": "Given that liberals and conservative voters run about equal in most elections with the winner winning by only a small margin of votes, I wonder if you mean, do they want to subside everyone\u2019s hedonism? The Trump vote was like not all conservative. Keep in mind, progressives who succumbed to the Russian propaganda and lies about HRC, probably voted for him, too. Statistics also show that those with higher education vote democrat. Is high education somehow associated with \u201chedonism\u201d? I think not. Here is a story that might explain liberalism to you. There was once a conservative man who had a lovely waterfront home and the water was sparkling clean and transparent. Then he began to find debris in his water, and the water got cloudy and he called experts in and they told him that the debris was coming from other home owners and businesses and even from over seas. The man was very irate because he loved his beautful blue water and it distressed him greatly to find medical debris and garbage on his pristine shores. He tried to build a dam around his property, and sand bars and put a net in the water to try to filter out the disgusting items and debris, but all the junk just caught on the net and it created a a barrier and the beach began to erode and in some areas there was stagnant water and a stench. The situation got worse and worse and no matter what he tried, the ocean outside his bedroom was no longer the joy it had been. He took down the barriers and stopped efforts to keep out the debris as he realized that the sea reaches everywhere and as long as there are ignorant, nasty people littering the earth and blighting our communities, we will all suffer. He began to see that most of the Earth\u2019s problems are related to the very same thing - lack of education, poverty, and the basest of human instincts, such as avarice and ego. In one word, Ignorance. With this realization, he became a liberal. ",
